                            <li><strong>Monument Signs:</strong> Ground-level signs made from durable materials such as stone, brick, or metal. Monument signs are commonly used at the entrances of businesses, schools, and residential communities. They provide a solid and professional appearance, welcoming visitors with a grand impression.</li>
                            <li><strong>Blade Signs:</strong> Mounted perpendicular to the building facade, blade signs are ideal for attracting pedestrian traffic. These signs can be illuminated and are often used in busy shopping districts. Blade signs catch the eye of passersby from different angles, drawing them towards your business.</li>
                            <li><strong>A-frame Signs:</strong> Portable, foldable signs that can be placed on sidewalks to attract foot traffic. A-frame signs are perfect for promoting daily specials, events, or new products. Their flexibility and ease of setup make them a versatile and cost-effective advertising tool.</li>
                            <li><strong>Menu Boards:</strong> Used in restaurants and cafes to display menu items and prices. Menu boards can be digital or printed and are essential for enhancing the dining experience. Clear and attractive menu boards help customers make informed choices and streamline the ordering process.</li>
